Hammer Dataset

1.Introduction

Researchers assessed the effect of spinal nerve ligation (SNL) on the transcriptome of rats. In this experiment, transcriptome profiling occurred at two weeks and two months after treatment, for both the SNL group and a control group. Two biological replicates are used for every treatment - time combination. The researchers are interested in early and late effects and in genes for which the effect changes over time.

omnibus hypothesis: screening stage

L<- matrix(0,ncol=3,nrow=4)
rownames(L)<-colnames(design)
colnames(L)<-c("early","late","inter")
L[3,1]<-1
L[3:4,2]<-1
L[4,3]<-1
L
                   early late inter
(Intercept)            0    0     0
time2m                 0    0     0
protocolsnl            1    1     0
time2m:protocolsnl     0    1     1
omnibus<-glmLRT(fit,contrast =L)

sigTests <- summary(dtOmnibus<-decideTests(omnibus))
alphaS1 <- (0.05 / sum(sigTests)) * (sigTests[2])  
alphaS1

Confirmation stage

  • We will combine all p-values for the contrasts of the second stage in a matrix (check if gene order is the same)
mean(rownames(early)==rownames(late))
mean(rownames(early)==rownames(inter))
pConfirmation<-cbind(early$table$PValue,late$table$PValue,inter$table$PValue)
fcConfirmation<-cbind(early$table$logFC,late$table$logFC,inter$table$logFC)
colnames(pConfirmation)<-colnames(fcConfirmation)<-colnames(L)
rownames(pConfirmation) <- rownames(fcConfirmation) <- rownames(early)
  • Adjusted p-values for FWER and only consider genes that passed screening stage.

Genes that do not pass screening stage will be set at 1.

pConfirmationAdj<-t(apply(pConfirmation,1,p.adjust,method="holm"))
pConfirmationAdj[dtOmnibus==0,] <- 1
dtConfirm <- (pConfirmationAdj < alphaS1) * sign(fcConfirmation)
class(dtConfirm) <- "TestResults"
summary(dtConfirm)
   early  late inter
-1  2955  3022   432
0   6736  7093 12281
1   3202  2778   180

Analysis with StageR

library(stageR)
pScreen <- omnibus$table$PValue
names(pScreen) <-rownames(omnibus)
stageRObj <- stageR(pScreen=pScreen,pConfirmation=pConfirmation, pScreenAdjusted=FALSE)
stageRObj <- stageWiseAdjustment(object=stageRObj, method="holm", alpha=0.05)
stageWiseRes <- getAdjustedPValues(stageRObj,onlySignificantGenes = TRUE,order = TRUE)
The returned adjusted p-values are based on a
                 stage-wise testing approach and are only valid for
                 the provided target OFDR level of 5%. If a different target OFDR level is of interest,
                 the entire adjustment should be re-run. 
colSums(stageWiseRes<0.05)
padjScreen      early       late      inter 
      7724       6289       5926        615

Analysis with StageR shaffer method

library(stageR)
pScreen <- omnibus$table$PValue
names(pScreen) <-rownames(omnibus)
stageRObj <- stageR(pScreen=pScreen,pConfirmation=pConfirmation, pScreenAdjusted=FALSE)
stageRObj <- stageWiseAdjustment(object=stageRObj, method="none", alpha=0.05)
stageWiseRes <- getAdjustedPValues(stageRObj,onlySignificantGenes = TRUE,order = TRUE)
